She can see dead people…she just chooses to ignore them. That’s Miko’s plan, anyway, but it doesn’t seem to be working for her in this love letter to the horror genre that will send shivers down your spine—and occasionally tickle your funny bone.
(Source: Funimation)

Thwarting a hijacking with the beautiful, silver-haired detective, Siesta, transforms Kimihiko’s young life. Their success kicks off years of crime-solving and confronting syndicates around the world—until Siesta dies. Left with questions, Kimihiko moves on. But now, a new case may open healed wounds as it connects to an assassin, a world conspiracy, and his dead partner! (Source: Funimation) Note: The first episode aired with a runtime of ~46 minutes as opposed to the standard 24 minute long episode.

Although Yuji Itadori looks like your average teenager, his immense physical strength is something to behold! Every sports club wants him to join, but Itadori would rather hang out with the school outcasts in the Occult Research Club. One day, the club manages to get their hands on a sealed cursed object. Little do they know the terror they’ll unleash when they break the seal… (Source: Viz Media) Note: Ranked 1st in Japan's Bookstore Employees Top Manga of 2018. Nominated to the 25th Annual Tezuka Osamu Cultural Prize.

Meet the would-be assassins of class 3-E: Sugino, who let his grades slip and got kicked off the baseball team. Karma, who’s doing well in his classes but keeps getting suspended for fighting. And Okuda, who lacks both academic and social skills, yet excels at one subject: chemistry. Who has the best chance of winning that reward? Will the deed be accomplished through pity, brute force or poison...? And what chance does their teacher have of repairing his students’ tattered self-esteem? (Source: Viz Media) Included Extra Chapters: Volume 1: Koro Sensei's Drawing Song Volume 2: Koro Sensei vs. Kusuo Saiki, Iruma City Battle Volume 7: Koro Sensei vs. Kusuo Saiki, Iruma City Battle II Volume 21: Time to Come Home Volume 21: Time to go to the Izakaya Volume 21: Time to Reveal Identities Volume 21: Time to Say Thank You Volume 21: Tokyo Department Store War Journal
